# Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Astro framework: https://docs.astro.build/llms-full.txt

## Code Style
- Write functional, immutable code
- Prefer pure functions and avoid side effects
- Use `const` over `let` when possible
- Avoid mutating data structures; create new ones instead
- Use array methods like `map`, `filter`, `reduce` instead of loops with mutations
- Do not use eslint-disable comments; fix the underlying issue instead

## Quality Checks
- At the end of every task, run and fix:
  - ESLint errors: `yarn eslint src --fix`
  - TypeScript errors: `yarn astro check`
